00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:09.000
And the way this works is a web technology known as WebAssembly. So WebAssembly has been

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:18.000
around since about 2017. And it's becoming more and more integrated into projects as

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:22.000
time goes on. Over the last couple of years, it's become very popular to add WebAssembly

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:28.000
support to your projects if they would work well on the web.

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:34.000
And what it is, is to give it the technical name, it's a portable binary code format. What

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:39.000
that means is that if you take a piece of code and you compile it for a machine, normally

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:42.000
it would only run on that machine. So you can take something like Python and compile

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:47.000
it for a Mac, and then it won't run on Windows, but it will run on your Mac machine.

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:51.000
The difference about WebAssembly is that it will run on those different types of machines

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:57.000
from a Mac, Windows, Linux, a phone, a tablet. It doesn't matter. As long as it has a web

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:03.000
browser that supports WebAssembly, it will run your code. And that's what portable means

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:11.000
in this context. And that makes things much more reproducible and easy to get into because

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:17.000
you can take this piece of code that's been compiled and run it anywhere very easily.

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:22.000
It's very high performance. It's almost as fast as running a traditional program on your

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:28.000
machine. And it's also supported by most modern web browsers. Chrome, Firefox, Safari

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:34.000
all support it. Edge, it works as well. And basically most modern web browsers will be

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:36.000
able to run WebAssembly code.

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:42.000
Now, it's interactive through JavaScript. So if you know JavaScript, you can use this

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:47.000
technology, this WebAssembly technology. But not everybody who knows Python or who knows

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:53.000
Azhar knows how to use JavaScript. And that's where things like Quarto extensions come in.

